The paper discusses secure architectures for distributed learning, which involves both cryptography and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also specifically mentions deep learning convolutional neural networks trained on medical images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of blockchain mechanisms, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper involves data privacy and equitable sharing, which could fall under the category of data science (cs.DS).
